description: Use muse to generate browser-ready technical diagrams, visual explainers, and review pages. Trigger on "diagram", "visual explainer", "visualize this", "visualize a plan", "make it visual", "explain this visually", diff review, plan review, project recap, slide deck, or complex comparison table.
globs: **/*
alwaysApply: false
---

Use the canonical `muse` skill from `plugins/Muse/`. Cursor support is rules-based guidance, not native Agent Skills support.

When the user asks for a diagram, architecture overview, diff review, plan review, project recap, slide deck, complex comparison table, or a "visual explainer" — or uses phrasings like "visualize this", "visualize a plan", "make it visual", "show me this visually", or "explain this visually" — read `plugins/Muse/skills/muse/SKILL.md` and follow its workflow. Use the command markdown in `plugins/Muse/commands/` as templates when helpful.

Write generated HTML to `.agents/diagrams/` unless the user asks for another path, then open it in a browser if Cursor permits shell/browser access. If browser access is blocked, report the file path.

Command palettes may not expose these templates directly in Cursor. `/share-page` requires the Pi-compatible `vercel-deploy` script, so treat sharing as optional and environment-dependent.
